{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8404caa6-e551-4273-b0e5-62cb244819ac","content":"In .NET MAUI, lifecycle handling moved from `Application` to `Window`. You subclass `Window` and override the corresponding methods:\n\n| Xamarin.Forms | .NET MAUI (Window) |\n|---|---|\n| `OnStart()` | `OnCreated()` |\n| `OnSleep()` | `OnStopped()` |\n| `OnResume()` | `OnResumed()` |\n\n**Example:**\n\n```csharp\npublic class MyWindow : Window\n{\n    public MyWindow(Page page) : base(page) { }\n\n    protected override void OnCreated()    { base.OnCreated();  /* start logic */ }\n    protected override void OnStopped()    { base.OnStopped();  /* sleep logic */ }\n    protected override void OnResumed()    { base.OnResumed();  /* resume logic */ }\n}\n```\n\nThen in your `App` class, override `CreateWindow`:\n\n```csharp\npublic partial class App : Application\n{\n    protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n        => new MyWindow(new MainPage());\n}\n```\n\n`Window` also provides `OnActivated()`, `OnDeactivated()`, and `OnDestroying()` for finer-grained control.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d53ea5b6-47c9-4c3c-94d8-cb9a71980ef9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating lifecycle methods from Xamarin.Forms to .NET MAUI. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.\n\nIn Xamarin.Forms, you'd override `OnStart()`, `OnSleep()`, and `OnResume()` in your `Application` subclass.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the lifecycle model changed. You use the `Window` lifecycle events or the cross-platform lifecycle events via `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`. But more directly, the `Window` class has `Created`, `Activated`, `Deactivated`, `Stopped`, `Resumed`, and `Destroying` events.\n \nFor the direct mapping, `OnStart` maps to the `Window.Created` event. In .NET MAUI, you can override `CreateWindow()` in your `Application` class to return a `Window` with lifecycle event handlers attached, subclass `Window` itself to override lifecycle methods, or use platform-specific lifecycle configuration through `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`.\n\nThe `Window` class provides overridable methods for `OnCreated()`, `OnActivated()`, `OnDeactivated()`, `OnStopped()`, `OnResumed()`, and `OnDestroying()`, which map to the old `Application` lifecycle events—`OnStart` becomes `Window.Created`, `OnSleep` becomes `Window.Stopped` or `Window.Deactivated`, and `OnResume` becomes `Window.Resumed` or `Window.Activated`.","outputTokens":897,"requestId":"1425:303613:6CDEBAA:752F012:6A03CD38"},"id":"2ebca083-b31e-43ce-a4d7-b6fdca32dfca","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:00:57.456Z","parentId":"79162630-1797-46e6-ad77-6b2ca2425b2a"}
